n on January 31, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/cw-renews-flash-charmed-riverdale-supernatural-6-more-1181714|title=CW Renews ''The Flash'', ''Charmed'', ''Riverdale'', ''Supernatural'', 6 More|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 31, 2019|accessdate=January 31, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190201020332/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/cw-renews-flash-charmed-riverdale-supernatural-6-more-1181714|archivedate=February 1, 2019}}</ref> In May 2019, ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' reported that co-executive producer Josh Reims would succeed co-creator [[Sallie Patrick]] as executive producer and showrunner for season three.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/dynasty-josh-reims-replace-sallie-patrick-new-showrunner-season-3-cw-series-1202622332/|title=''Dynasty'': Josh Reims to Succeed Co-Creator Sallie Patrick as New Showrunner For Season 3 of the CW Series|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 25, 2019|accessdate=May 29, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526005037/https://deadline.com/2019/05/dynasty-josh-reims-replace-sallie-patrick-new-showrunner-season-3-cw-series-1202622332/|archivedate=May 26, 2019}}</ref> On January 7, 2020, ''Dynasty'' was renewed for a fourth season.<ref name=\"S4 Deadline\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/the-cw-renews-13-series-batwoman-nancy-drew-the-flash-riverdale-all-american-1202823557/|title=The CW Renews 13 Series Including ''Batwoman'', ''Nancy Drew'', ''The Flash'', ''Riverdale'', ''All American''|website=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Nellie|last1=Andreeva|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200107231427/https://deadline.com/2020/01/the-cw-renews-13-series-batwoman-nancy-drew-the-flash-riverdale-all-american-1202823557/|archivedate=January 7, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"S4 TVL\">{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2020/01/07/the-cw-renewed-shows-2020-list-riverdale-flash/|title=CW Renews ''Riverdale'', ''Batwoman'', ''Roswell'', ''Black Lightning'' Plus 9 Others|website=TVLine|first1=Michael|last1=Ausiello|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108032431/https://tvline.com/2020/01/07/the-cw-renewed-shows-2020-list-riverdale-flash/|archivedate=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn July 2019, it was announced that [[Ana Brenda Contreras]] would not be returning for season three for personal reasons, and that [[Daniella Alonso]] would take over the role of Cristal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/07/29/dynasty-recast-daniella-alonso-cristal-ana-brenda-contreras/|title=''Dynasty'' Recast: Daniella Alonso Joins Season 3 as New Cristal Jennings|first=Andy|last=Swift|work=TVLine|date=July 30, 2019|accessdate=July 30, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190730010941/https://tvline.com/2019/07/29/dynasty-recast-daniella-alonso-cristal-ana-brenda-contreras/|archivedate=July 30, 2019}}</ref> In August 2019 it was reported that [[Michael Michele]] had been promoted to a series regular for the third season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvshowsace.com/2019/08/09/dynasty-who-is-returning-to-cw-show-for-season-3/|title=''Dynasty'': Who Is Returning To CW Show For Season 3?|work=TVShowsAce.com|date=August 9, 2019 |accessdate=August 10, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810130606/https://www.tvshowsace.com/2019/08/09/dynasty-who-is-returning-to-cw-show-for-season-3/|archivedate=August 10, 2019}}</ref> and it was announced in October 2019 that Adam Huber had been promoted to a series regular as well.<ref name=\"S3NewRegulars\"/><ref name=\"TVLine S3NewRegulars\"/> On September 5, 2019, Ken Kirby was announced to be joining the show in a recurring role as Evan Tate, Trixie's older brother.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/ken-kirby-dynasty-the-cw-recurring-chelsea-rendon-shameless-showtime-1202711179/|title=Ken Kirby Joins ''Dynasty'' In Recurring Role; Chelsea Rendon Boards ''Shameless''|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Dino-Ray|last=Ramos|date=September 5, 2019|archivedate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> [[Kelli Barrett]] and Jade Payton also joined the show in recurring roles, Barrett acting as Adam's nurse, Nadia, and Payton portraying Dominique's stepdaughter, Vanessa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiddenremote.com/2019/11/09/dynasty-power-rankings-s3e5/|title=''Dynasty'' power rankings: Is it too late for Liam to finally, fully remember Fallon?|website=Hidden Remote|first=Reed|last=Gaudens|date=November 9, 2019|archivedate=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn October 28, 2019, it was announced that the role of [[Alexis Colby|Alexis Carrington]] had been recast with [[Elaine Hendrix]], who would appear as a series regular.<ref name=\"ElaineH\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/dynasty-new-alexis-elaine-hendrix-cast-cw-joan-collins-1202770394/|title=''Dynasty'' Casts Elaine Hendrix as the New Alexis for CW Soap|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Dominic|last=Patten|date=October 28, 2019|accessdate=October 28, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028171221/https://deadline.com/2019/10/dynasty-new-alexis-elaine-hendrix-cast-cw-joan-collins-1202770394/|archivedate=October 28, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TVLine Hendrix\">{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/10/28/dynasty-cast-elaine-hendrix-alexis-recast-season-3/|title=''Dynasty'' Casts Elaine Hendrix as the New Alexis Carrington in Season 3|first=Andy|last=Swift|website=TVLine|date=October 28, 2019|accessdate=October 29, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028163452/https://tvline.com/2019/10/28/dynasty-cast-elaine-hendrix-alexis-recast-season-3/|archivedate=October 28, 2019}}</ref> The CW noted that \"Alexis is back in Atlanta, with a new look, a new man, and plenty of scores to settle\".<ref name=\"TVLine Hendrix\"/> Hendrix debuted as Alexis in \"[[The Sensational Blake Carrington Trial]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/12/04/dynasty-season-3-new-alexis-elaine-hendrix-first-photo/|title=''Dynasty'' First Look: Elaine Hendrix Debuts as the New Alexis Carrington|first=Andy|last=Swift|website=TVLine|date=December 4, 2019|accessdate=December 5, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204194101/https://tvline.com/2019/12/04/dynasty-season-3-new-alexis-elaine-hendrix-first-photo/|archivedate=December 4, 2019}}</ref> In February 2020, it was announced that [[Wil Traval]] had been cast to recur as Father Caleb Collins, a \"young, charming and irreverent priest with a soft spot for the disabled vets who rehab in the hospital's clinic.\" He has been teased as a potential love interest for Cristal Carrington.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2020/02/27/this-is-us-season-4-episode-18-strangers-part-2-finale/|title=Ask Ausiello: Scoop on ''This Is Us'', ''Lucifer'', ''TWD'', ''Zoey's'', ''Schitt's Creek'', ''Chicago PD'', ''Million Little'' and More|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|website=TVLine|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcast==\nSeason three of ''Dynasty'' premiered on October 11, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/the-cw-sets-fall-premiere-dates-batwoman-supergirl-the-flash-nancy-drew-1202633821/|title=The CW Sets Fall Premiere Dates: ''Batwoman'', ''Supergirl'', ''The Flash'', ''Nancy Drew'', More|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=June 17, 2019|accessdate=June 17, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617211029/https://deadline.com/2019/06/the-cw-sets-fall-premiere-dates-batwoman-supergirl-the-flash-nancy-drew-1202633821/|archivedate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width    = 99\n| fontsize = 90\n\n| title1   = [[#ep45|Guilt Trip to Alaska]]\n