onso]] as Blake's new wife [[Cristal Carrington|Cristal]], and [[Sam Underwood]] as Blake's eldest son [[Adam Carrington]], with [[Robert Christopher Riley]] as former chauffeur [[Michael Culhane]], [[Sam Adegoke]] as tech billionaire [[Jeff Colby]], [[Rafael de la Fuente]] as [[Sam Jones (Dynasty)|Sam Jones]], Fallon's half-brother [[Steven Carrington|Steven]]'s ex-husband, Adam Huber as Fallon's fianc\u00e9 [[Liam Ridley]], [[Alan Dale]] as [[Joseph Anders]], the Carrington [[majordomo]], [[Maddison Brown]] as Anders's daughter [[Kirby Anders|Kirby]], and [[Michael Michele]] as [[Dominique Deveraux]], Blake's half-sister and the mother of Jeff and [[Monica Colby]] (Wakeema Hollis). [[Elaine Hendrix]] portrays Blake's ex-wife [[Alexis Carrington]], the mother of Adam, [[Steven Carrington|Steven]] and Fallon.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{See also|List of Dynasty (2017 TV series) characters}}\n[[File:Daniella Alonso at the 2014 Alma Awards.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Daniella Alonso]] portrays Cristal in season three.]]\n[[File:Elaine Hendrix speaking at the 2015 San Diego Comic-Con International (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|[[Elaine Hendrix]] plays [[Alexis Colby|Alexis Carrington]] in season three.]]\n\n===Main===\n* [[Elizabeth Gillies]] as [[Fallon Carrington]], energy executive and heiress to an Atlanta energy fortune, daughter of billionaire Blake Carrington and his first wife, Alexis\n* [[Daniella Alonso]] as [[Cristal Jennings|Cristal Jennings Carrington]], a close friend of Blake's late second wife who becomes his third wife\n* [[Rafael de La Fuente]] as [[Sam Jones (Dynasty)|Samuel Josiah \"Sammy Jo\" Jones Carrington]], nephew of Blake's second wife Cristal, and [[Steven Carrington|Steven]]'s ex-husband\n* [[Sam Underwood]] as [[Adam Carrington]], Blake and Alexis's eldest son, a doctor who was kidnapped as an infant\n* [[Michael Michele]] as [[Dominique Deveraux]],<ref name=\"S3NewRegulars\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/dynasty-daniella-alonso-promoted-series-regular-cristal-jennings-role-michael-michele-sam-underwood-adam-huber-1202757278/|title=''Dynasty'': Daniella Alonso Upped To Series Regular In Cristal Role; Michael Michele, Sam Underwood, Adam Huber Also Promoted|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=October 11, 2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011200552/https://deadline.com/2019/10/dynasty-daniella-alonso-promoted-series-regular-cristal-jennings-role-michael-michele-sam-underwood-adam-huber-1202757278/|archivedate=October 11, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TVLine S3NewRegulars\">{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/10/11/dynasty-season-3-cast-changes-new-series-regulars/|title=''Dynasty'' Sets New Series Regulars Ahead of Season 3 Premiere|website=[[TVLine]]|first=Andy|last=Swift|date=October 11, 2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011181109/https://tvline.com/2019/10/11/dynasty-season-3-cast-changes-new-series-regulars/|archivedate=October 11, 2019}}</ref> Jeff and Monica's mother and Blake's half-sister\n* [[Robert Christopher Riley]] as [[Michael Culhane]], Fallon's ex-fianc\u00e9, formerly the Carrington chauffeur\n* [[Sam Adegoke]] as [[Jeff Colby]], a young business rival to Blake eventually revealed to be his nephew\n* [[Maddison Brown]] as [[Kirby Anders]], Joseph's daughter and Sam's best friend\n* Adam Huber as [[Liam Ridley]],<ref name=\"S3NewRegulars\"/><ref name=\"TVLine S3NewRegulars\"/> Fallon's former husband and new fianc\u00e9\n* [[Alan Dale]] as [[Joseph Anders]], the Carrington majordomo\n* [[Grant Show]] as [[Blake Carrington]], widowed billionaire and the father of Adam and Fallon by his first wife, [[Alexis Colby|Alexis]]\n* [[Elaine Hendrix]] as [[Alexis Colby|Alexis Carrington Colby]],{{efn|Hendrix is credited as a regular beginning in \"[[The Sensational Blake Carrington Trial]]\".}} Blake's ex-wife, Jeff's current wife and Adam, Steven, and Fallon's mother.\n\n===Recurring===\n* Wakeema Hollis as [[Monica Colby]], Jeff's sister<!-- 301, 303, 304, 306, 307, 308 -->\n* [[Sharon Lawrence]] as [[Laura Van Kirk]], Liam's mother<!-- 302, 304, 316, 317 -->\n* [[Kelli Barrett]] as Nadia, Adam's physical therapist<!-- 305, 306, 307, 308 -->\n* Jade Payton as [[Vanessa Deveraux]], an aspiring singer who is Dominique's stepdaughter and Jeff and Monica's stepsister<!-- 305, 306, 307, 308, 312, 314, 315, 317 -->\n* [[Daniel Di Tomasso]] as Fletcher Myers, a public relations consultant who helps Sam at La Mirage<!-- 307, 309, 310, 311, 313 -->\n* Emily Rudd as Heidi, Liam's former girlfriend and the mother of his brother Connor<!-- 313, 314, 315, 316 -->\n* John Jackson Hunter as Connor, Liam's brother who he initially believes is his son<!-- 313, 314, 315, 316 -->\n\n===Guest===\n* Taylor Black as Ashley Cunningham, Liam's ex-girlfriend<!-- 301, 302 -->\n* Jessi Goei as Trixie Tate, a childhood friend of Fallon's who was killed at Carrington Manor<!-- 301 -->\n* Rob Nagle as Mitchell, Blake's lawyer<!-- 302, 308, 309 -->\n* [[Kelly Rutherford]] as Melissa Daniels, Steven's former lover<!-- 303 -->\n* Ken Kirby as Evan Tate,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/ken-kirby-dynasty-the-cw-recurring-chelsea-rendon-shameless-showtime-1202711179/|title=Ken Kirby Joins ''Dynasty'' in Recurring Role; Chelsea Rendon Boards ''Shameless''|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Dino-Ray|last=Ramos|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=October 10, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905201850/https://deadline.com/2019/09/ken-kirby-dynasty-the-cw-recurring-chelsea-rendon-shameless-showtime-1202711179/|archivedate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> Trixie's older brother<!-- 303, 305, 306 -->\n* Chase Anderson as Tony, the Carrington gardener<!-- 303, 308, 310 -->\n* Natalie Karp as Mrs. Gunnerson, the Carrington cook<!-- 304, 308 -->\n* Christian Ochoa as Victor, a new Atlantix player<!-- 304, 305 -->\n* [[Ashanti (singer)|Ashanti]] as herself<!-- 305 -->\n* [[Pierson Fod\u00e9]] as Joel Turner, a motivational speaker who becomes involved with Kirby<!-- 306, 310 -->\n* [[Chukwudi Iwuji]] as Landon, a creative director and old friend of Liam<!-- 307 -->\n* [[Erin Cummings]] as District Attorney Erica Brown, the prosecutor in Blake's murder trial<!-- 308, 309 -->\n* Nicole Zyana as Allison, Fallon's assistant<!-- 311, 317 -->\n* Keller Wortham as Jacks Davis, Fallon's real estate agent<!-- 312 -->\n* [[Lilli Cooper]] as Stacey, a reality show producer who meets with Dominique<!-- 313, 314 -->\n* [[Geovanni Gopradi]] as Roberto \"Beto\" Flores, Cristal's brother<!-- 314, 315 -->\n* [[Wil Traval]] as Father Caleb Collins, a priest who is the new hospital chaplain<!-- 316, 317 -->\n* Mustafa Elzein as Ramy Crockett, Sam's criminal friend from season one<!-- 316, 317 -->\n;Cast notes\n{{notelist}}\n{{clear}}\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>\n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=24 |director=15 |writer=32 |airdate=12 |viewers=8 |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|Dynasty (2017 TV series, season 3)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 45\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Guilt Trip to Alaska\n |DirectedBy      = [[Michael A. Allowitz]]\n |WrittenBy       = Josh Reims\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|11}}\n |Viewers         = 0.45<ref name=\"3.01\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/friday-final-ratings-oct-11-2019/|title=''Blue Bloods'' adjusts down: Friday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=October 14, 2019|accessdate=October 14, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191014204419/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/friday-final-ratings-oct-11-2019/|archivedate=October 14, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The Carringtons deal with the discovery of the bodies in the lake. As Liam lies in a coma, Fallon begins seeing Trixie everywhere she goes. Adam tries to kill Liam in the hospital, but is interrupted by Fallon. Ashley arrives, and when Liam wakes up, he does not remember Fallon. Dominique plays the worried mother for the press, but still claims her payoff from Blake for getting Jeff out of town. Sam begins renovating his hotel, and Blake kicks Kirby out of the Manor. Adam sneaks into the morgue and arranges for Mack's body to be cremated, but Blake is arrested anyway. Fallon confesses to the police that Trixie's fall was an accident, and lies that Mack disposed of the body on his own.\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Dynasty (2017 TV series, season 3)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 46\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Caution Never Won a War\n |DirectedBy      = [[Melanie Mayron]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[David M. Israel]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|18}}\n |Viewers         = 0.41<ref name=\"3.02\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/friday-final-ratings-oct-18-2019/|title=''20/20'', ''Dateline'', and ''WWE SmackDown'' adjust down: Friday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 21, 2019|accessdate=October 21, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021220813/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/friday-final-ratings-oct-18-2019/|archivedate=October 21, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Blake is booked, the police having found his DNA inside Mack's body bag. Fallon pulls out all the stops to get Liam to remember her, but his mother Laura does her best to thwart Fallon's efforts. Sam and Anders discover that the hotel is historically significant. Sam arranges a media day to capitalize on this fact, only to learn that the hotel's famous designer was an outspoken homophobe. Adam outmaneuvers Cristal to be named temporary CEO of Blake's winery. In jail, Michael tries to intimidate Blake to goad him into incriminating himself. When Blake is overheard threatening to have Michael du