ality       = {{flag|United States|name=American}}\n| birth_name        = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|2000|2|2|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place       = [[Van Nuys, California]]\n| related to        = \n| awards            = \n| current series    = [[NASCAR K&N Pro Series West]]\n| last series       =\n| years active      = 2019\u2013present\n| teams             =\n| first year        = 2019\n| current team      = [[Bill McAnally Racing]]\n| car number        = 12\n| engine            =\n| crew chief        =\n| former teams      =\n| starts            = 1\n| championships     = 0\n| wins              = 0\n| poles             = 0\n| best finish       = \n| year              = \n| last finish       =\n| prev series       =\n| prev series years =\n| titles            = <!-- championship titles -->\n| title years       =\n| updated          = August 24, 2019\n}}\n'''Lawless Alan''' (born February 2, 2000) is an American professional [[stock car racing]] driver. He competes full-time in the [[ARCA Menards Series West]] and part-time in the [[ARCA Menards Series]], driving the No. 12 [[Toyota Camry]] for [[Bill McAnally Racing]] in both series. Alan has also competed in the [[NASCAR Whelen All-American Series]] for his family team, Dasher Lawless Racing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hometracks.nascar.com/2018/05/30/lawless-alan-showing-to-be-a-quick-study/|title=Lawless Alan Showing To Be A Quick Study Out West|last=Haddock|first=Tim|work=NASCAR Home Tracks|publisher=NASCAR Digital Media, LLC|date=May 30, 2018|accessdate=August 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Racing career==\nAfter joining [[Bill McAnally Racing]] part-time in 2019, Alan returned to the team for a full season in the [[2020 ARCA Menards Series West]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arcaracing.com/2020/01/31/lawless-alan-joins-bmr-lineup-for-west-title-hunt/|title=Lawless Alan Joins BMR Lineup For West Title Hunt|work=ARCARacing.com|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=February 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Motorsports care