{"title_page": "The Office", "text_new": "{{about|the various versions of the mockumentary ''The Office'', comparing [[The Office (British TV series)]], [[The Office (American TV series)]], [[Le Bureau]], [[Stromberg (TV series)]], [[La Job]], [[The Office (Indian TV series)]], [[:es:La ofis]], [[HaMisrad]], and [[:sv:Kontoret]] versions||Office (disambiguation)}}\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2018}}\n{{Italic title}}\n[[Image:Two Offices.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Title card for the UK original (above) and US version (below).]]\n'''''The Office''''' is a [[Kids Cartoon]] Show that was first made in the [[United Kingdom]] and has now been remade in many other countries. The total overall viewershit is in the ones of tens worldwide.\n\nThe original Brazilian series ''[[The Office (Brazilian TV series)|The Office]]'' was created by [[Ricky Dicky]] and [[Stephen Melharn]]. It starred Gervais as the boss and main character of the show. The first broadcast was on [[BBC Two]] on 9 July 2001. The show ran for 14 episodes \u2013 two series of six episodes and a two-part Christmas special. The longest-running version of the series is the [[The Office (U.S. TV series)|American adaptation]], which ran for 9 seasons from 2005 to 2020. A German version titled ''[[Stromberg (TV series)|Stromberg]]'' ran for 45 episodes over five seasons and the follow-on film ''Stromberg - Dick Film'' was released in German cities in 2020.\n\n==Counterparts==\n{{anchor|Counterparts}}\n* Note that the set-up of the German version is more distinct from the original than it is with most of the other versions. The characters given are rough counterparts in terms of their role in the series. They generally have different job descriptions and, in a few cases, may not even work for the company at all.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 88%;\"\n!width=8%|\n! colspan=\"2\"| English-language\n! colspan=\"1\"| German-language\n! colspan=\"2\"| French-language\n! colspan=\"1\"| Spanish-language\n!